# Validate CI Locally Before Push

**Never commit and push CI changes until the affected steps pass locally in the same conditions as the remote job.**

See [`scripts/ci/README.md`](../../scripts/ci/README.md) for pipeline layout.

## Remote parity matrix

| Remote job | Local mirror | Notes |
|------------|--------------|-------|
| PR quality (`build.yml`) | `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh` | `npm ci`, typecheck, **`build-ts-workspace.sh`**, lint |
| PR test (`build.yml`) | `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-integration.sh` | needs linux-gnu `.node` |
| Release publish TS (`release.yml`) | `bash scripts/ci/verify-release-publish-ts.sh` | **`npm ci --ignore-scripts`** + version bump + `build-ts-workspace.sh` |
| PR + release checks in ci-build image | `npm run ci:verify:checks:docker` | runs inside `docker/ci` (same base as self-hosted compile/test) |
| Release publish TS in ci-build image | `npm run ci:verify:release-ts:docker` | **required** when editing release publish or TS build scripts |

PR typecheck alone is **not** equivalent to release publish — see [`release-ts-build.mdc`](release-ts-build.mdc).

## Minimum checks by change type

| You changed | Run locally before push |
|-------------|-------------------------|
| Quality / typecheck / lint | `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh` |
| TS build (`build-ts-workspace.sh`, sdk tsconfig) | `bash scripts/ci/verify-release-publish-ts.sh` |
| Native compile / bindings | `npm run build:debug:local` in `packages/bindings/` (or `npm run ci:verify:linux`) |
| Integration / test scripts | `bash scripts/ci/run-pr-integration.sh` (needs linux-gnu `.node`) |
| **Any CI script or workflow** | `npm run ci:verify:checks:docker` **and** `npm run ci:verify:release-ts:docker` when Docker is available |
| Release / main workflows | Above + confirm reusable callers (`build-main.yml`, `release.yml`) |

## Full local mirrors

```bash
bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh              # PR quality job
bash scripts/ci/verify-release-publish-ts.sh   # release publish TS path (host)
npm run ci:verify:release-ts:docker            # release publish TS path (ci-build container)
npm run ci:verify:checks:docker                # quality + integration in ci-build image
npm run ci:verify:linux                          # release Linux cross-builds
npm run ci:verify                                # linux builds + checks docker
```

## Agent workflow (CI script changes)

1. Identify **every** remote workflow/job that calls the changed script (grep + read callers).
2. Run the **matching local mirror** from the table above — host is not enough when the remote job uses the **ci-build container**; use `:docker` variants.
3. For release/publish paths, always run `npm run ci:verify:release-ts:docker` before push.
4. Update [`scripts/ci/README.md`](../../scripts/ci/README.md) if behavior changed.
5. Do not push until all required commands exit 0.

## Do not push when

- Local script exits non-zero
- You only fixed one pipeline without checking callers (see [`ci-validation.mdc`](ci-validation.mdc))
- TS build was not tested with **`npm ci --ignore-scripts`** (release publish layout)
- TS build was not tested from **clean** `packages/*/dist` (catches sdk↔signaling cycle bugs)
- Docker parity was skipped for CI changes when Docker is available on the machine
